Hi John,

I hope this finds you well.  Haim has asked that I reach out to you in the =
hopes that you could provide some guidance or a recommendation for the pote=
ntial hiring of an Executive Director (title TBD) to develop a strategy to =
combat the Boycott, Divestment, Sanctions (BDS) movement.  A key focus woul=
d be increasing pro-Israel student participation in student government.

I'm including below a brief  job description in case someone comes to mind.

Thanks in advance for your guidance.

Best,
Laura

________________________________

Goal: To retain a seasoned campaign strategist "Executive Director" to deve=
lop a plan (and then execute on it) to combat BDS, especially on college ca=
mpuses.  A key focus would be providing the campaign training and tools for=
 pro-Israel student participation in and engagement with student government=
s.

As background, the below outlines the key responsibilities and qualificatio=
ns:

Key responsibilities

*  Conceive and implement a high impact strategy to combat the BDS movement=
.
*  Leverage and amplify the efforts of existing anti-BDS organizations.
*  Hire, manage and coordinate the professional and leadership resources ne=
ed to execute the strategy.
*  Drive social media strategy and efforts as well as decisive action deriv=
ed from the media efforts (Organizing active anti-BDS efforts).

The Executive Director Will Possess the Following Personal and Professional=
 Characteristics:
* Strong commitment to Israel and rich knowledge of key issues facing Israe=
l and facing world Jewry.
* Entrepreneurial leadership with demonstrated ability to start up and grow=
 an organization.
* Demonstrated large system savvy.
* Ability and willingness to initiate and engage contacts at high levels
* Mediator and cajoler who can bring groups together around a common cause.
* Resourceful.
* Able to work up and down age groups from college campuses to senior execu=
tives and government officials.
* Out of the box thinker and operator.
* Social media and technology savvy.
* High energy.
* Demonstrated commitment to excellence.

Past Experience:
Entrepreneur, Company CEO; High level diplomat, University President, Senio=
r military leader.


